                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d252">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115 PW/8–245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-08T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 8, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2492. Inform Swiss that Department is seriously concerned by use of term hostage
                    in your 3777 August 2. Suggestion has been made by a reliable neutral long
                    resident in Tokyo that Japanese savagery might be vented upon POWs as war goes
                    against Japan. Department desires to receive any information Swiss may receive
                    in this regard.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
